^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let's first discuss DONT. Bergen recommends that you show a single suited hand only when you have a six card suit. I don't happen to agree. I think you can do it with a reasonable 5 card suit. And having said that Bergen also says "any suit with 4 honors can be counted as having 1 card extra length." So since Eileen's heart suit has 4 honors, Bergen says it is ok to treat it as a six card suit. I would bid DONT even lacking the @H10. I think DONT is an extremely effective convention, so I use it with any excuse.|
