Noah121:  How strong should your hand be in order to use DONT?|
PG| ***** 56 ***** |


cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The distribution is more important than the length, but here are my guidelines. If you have a six card suit that you would open a weak-2, it is ok to show a single suited hand. If you are 5-5 you can have as little as 7 HCP where your points are in your suit. If you are 5-4 you should tend to have a bit more, say 10 or 11. And with an opening hand, I sometimes do it even with 4-4, if both my suits are good suits.|
